{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:job.3",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 3",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 3 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.3.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:1",
      "text": "After this Job opened his mouth, and cursed his day,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.3.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:2",
      "text": "saying,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.3.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:3",
      "text": "Let the day perish in which I was born, and that night in which they said, Behold a man-child!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.3.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:4",
      "text": "Let that night be darkness, and let not the Lord regard it from above, neither let light come upon it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.3.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:5",
      "text": "But let darkness and the shadow of death seize it; let blackness come upon it;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.3.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:6",
      "text": "let that day and night be cursed, let darkness carry them away; let it not come into the days of the year, neither let it be numbered with the days of the months.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.3.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:7",
      "text": "But let that night be pain, and let not mirth come upon it, nor joy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.3.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:8",
      "text": "But let him that curses that day curse it, even he that is ready to attack the great whale.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.3.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:9",
      "text": "Let the stars of that night be darkened; let it remain dark, and not come into light; and let it not see the morning star arise:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.3.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:10",
      "text": "because it shut not up the gates of my mother's womb, for so it would have removed sorrow from my eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.3.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:11",
      "text": "For why died I not in the belly? and why did I not come forth from the womb and die immediately?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.3.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:12",
      "text": "And why did the knees support me? and why did I suck the breasts?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.3.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:13",
      "text": "Now I should have lain down and been quiet, I should have slept and been at rest,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.3.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:14",
      "text": "with kings and councillors of the earth, who gloried in their swords;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.3.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:15",
      "text": "or with rulers, whose gold was abundant, who filled their houses with silver:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.3.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:16",
      "text": "or I should have been as an untimely birth proceeding from his mother's womb, or as infants who never saw light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.3.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:17",
      "text": "There the ungodly have burnt out the fury of rage; there the wearied in body rest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.3.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:18",
      "text": "And the men of old time have together ceased to hear the exactor's voice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.3.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:19",
      "text": "The small and great are there, and the servant that feared his lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.3.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:20",
      "text": "For why is light given to those who are in bitterness, and life to the souls which are in griefs?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.3.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:21",
      "text": "who desire death, and obtain it not, digging for it as for treasures;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.3.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:22",
      "text": "and would be very joyful if they should gain it?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.3.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:23",
      "text": "Death is rest to such a man, for God has hedged him in.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.3.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:24",
      "text": "For my groaning comes before my food, and I weep being beset with terror.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.3.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:25",
      "text": "For the terror of which I meditated has come upon me, and that which I had feared has befallen me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.3.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:26",
      "text": "I was not at peace, nor quiet, nor had I rest; yet wrath came upon me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
